719787f-a.title: Manhattan: Forsyth Street - Houston Street (East)
719787f-a.text:
Forsyth Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.W. corner of East
Houston Street. Also shown are Nos. 133-129 East Houston Street, at, adjoin-
ing and west of the S.W. corner of Forsyth Street.
July 18, 1929.
P.1L. Sperc.
719787f-a.folder: Forsyth Street & Houston Street (East), Manhattan, NY

719475f-a.title: Manhattan: Houston Street (East) - Forsyth Street
719475f-a.text:
East Houston Street, south side, east from (No. 97), but not
including the Bowery, to and including Forsyth Street, showing
consecutively, part of the 11-story Fisher Building (Nos. 97-103);
St. Augustine's Chapel (Trinity Parish) at Nos. 105-109; and the
National (formerly Tomashefsky) Theatre, Nos. 111-117, at the S.W.
corner of Chrystie Street. Also shown (foreground) is construction
work in progress (north side of the street) on the Independent System
Subway (Eighth Ave. subway), after demolition of the houses which
formerly occupied the site. In the background is visible a clearance
between Chrystie and Forsyth Streets, now (1937) part of the Sarah
Delano Roosevelt Park.
October 18, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
